                        <interp inst="t17831029-23-person370" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  , Esq; and that certain wages and pay were due from our said Lord the King to the said 
                     <persName id="t17831029-23-person371">
                        John
                         Hopkins
                     <interp inst="t17831029-23-person371" type="surname" value="Hopkins"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17831029-23-person371" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17831029-23-person371" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  , for his service on board the said ship, on the <rs id="t17831029-23-cd127" type="crimeDate">21st day of June</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17831029-23-off126 t17831029-23-cd127"></join> last, falsly and feloniously did forge and counterfeit, and cause and procure to be forged and counterfeited a certain letter of attorney, with a certain mark thereunto set, purporting to be the mark of the said 
                     <persName id="t17831029-23-person372">
                        John
                         Hopkins
                     <interp inst="t17831029-23-person372" type="surname" value="Hopkins"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17831029-23-person372" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17831029-23-person372" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  , and which said letter of attorney purported to be signed, sealed, and delivered by the said 
                     <persName id="t17831029-23-person373">
                        John
                         Hopkins
                     <interp inst="t17831029-23-person373" type="surname" value="Hopkins"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17831029-23-person373" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17831029-23-person373" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  , in order to receive the said wages and pay, then due from our said Lord the King to the<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="178310290070"></xptr> said 
                     <persName id="t17831029-23-person374">
                        John
                         Hopkins
                     <interp inst="t17831029-23-person374" type="surname" value="Hopkins"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17831029-23-person374" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17831029-23-person374" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  , as a <rs id="t17831029-23-viclabel128" type="occupation">seaman</rs>
                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17831029-23-victim376 t17831029-23-viclabel128"></join> on board the said ship, with intention to defraud the said 
                     
                        <persName id="t17831029-23-victim376" type="victimName">
                           John 
                           Hopkins
                        <interp inst="t17831029-23-victim376" type="surname" value="Hopkins"></interp>
